timeline.bodyText:
as this must happen to work correctly I'd think bootstrap should be final and another abstract method is introduced that is called here after configuration is initialised. Possibly passing the configuration as an argument like:
 protected abstract void bootstrap(NC configuration);
which then is implemented by the extending class - this circumvents wrong extension and spares the developer extending this class to understand the exact mechanics of the configuration bootstrap.

